    description: {
      en: 'Reported via the bug form (2026-06-21). Confirmed against `Eldar ENG.ods` "Armory" sheet: every weapon/equipment item has TWO separate price columns, "POINTS PSYKER" and "POINTS AUTARCH" — many are "-" (unavailable) in one column and priced in the other (e.g. Witchblade: 8 Psyker / "-" Autarch; Aspect armor: "-" Psyker / 12 Autarch). Initially assumed this meant the data needed a migration (new p_char_psyker/p_char_autarch fields) — turned out NOT to be a data problem at all: cross-checking all 58 split items confirmed `p_unit` already exactly equals the Psyker price and `p_char` already exactly equals the Autarch price for every single one, with zero mismatches (the original parser had already mapped the .ods\'s two columns onto the schema\'s two numeric slots correctly, just non-obviously named). The REAL bug was purely in `components/ArmoryModal.tsx`\'s `getItemPts`, which always preferred `p_char` for ANY character buyer (`cp ?? up`) regardless of whether that character was a Psyker or an Autarch. FIXED (2026-06-21): added a `resolveEldarCharPrice` helper that picks `p_unit` (Psyker column) or `p_char` (Autarch column) by `unit.is_psyker`, applied only when `activeData.faction === \'Eldar\' && isChar` — every other faction\'s p_unit/p_char keep their normal squad/character meaning untouched. A squad buyer (e.g. a Warlocks unit, is_psyker:true) was already pricing correctly off `p_unit` by coincidence (since p_unit IS the Psyker column), so that path needed no change.',
      de: 'Gemeldet über das Bug-Formular (2026-06-21). Bestätigt gegen das "Armory"-Blatt von Eldar ENG.ods. War KEIN Datenproblem: p_unit entsprach bereits exakt dem Psyker-Preis, p_char dem Autarch-Preis für alle 58 Items. Der eigentliche Fehler lag in getItemPts, das immer p_char bevorzugte, unabhängig von der Rolle. FIXED (2026-06-21): neue resolveEldarCharPrice-Funktion, nur für Eldar-Charaktere.',
      es: 'Reportado vía el formulario de bugs (2026-06-21). Confirmado contra la hoja "Armory" de Eldar ENG.ods. NO era un problema de datos: p_unit ya coincidía exactamente con el precio Psyker y p_char con el de Autarch en los 58 ítems. El error real estaba en getItemPts, que siempre prefería p_char sin importar el rol. ARREGLADO (2026-06-21): nueva función resolveEldarCharPrice, aplicada solo a personajes de Eldar.',
    },
