      en: 'Found 2026-06-20 via ODS audit. Re-confirmed 2026-06-21: Geminae Superia\'s OPTIONS line reads "For every Living Saint, the army may include one Geminae Superia unit that does not take up an HQ slot." FIXED (2026-06-21) with a new `computeGeminaeSuperiaFreeSlots` (validators.ts), mirroring computeAssassinFreeSlots/computeEldarWarlockFreeSlots\' "collapse N flagged entries → a slot credit" shape: counts Geminae Superia and Living Saint entries army-wide and credits min(geminae, livingSaints) HQ slots automatically (the ods phrasing grants it outright, no per-instance opt-in needed, same as the Assassins\' rule) — wired into the same `slotAdj` HQ-slot calculation `cdFree.hq` already uses. The unit\'s own placeholder option group is left as descriptive text only (same precedent as the C\'tan Shard "unique" placeholder this week) — enforcement lives in the validator, not a non-functional toggle.',
      de: 'Gefunden am 2026-06-20 per ODS-Audit. FIXED (2026-06-21) mit computeGeminaeSuperiaFreeSlots (validators.ts) — zählt Geminae-Superia- und Living-Saint-Einheiten armeeweit und gewährt automatisch min(geminae, livingSaints) HQ-Slot-Gutschriften, verdrahtet in dieselbe HQ-Slot-Berechnung, die cdFree.hq bereits nutzt.',
