    description: 'Found 2026-06-19 via live builder exploration (Chaos Ogryn stepper showed "/3" available with only 10 Traitor Guardsmen in the squad, when the rule is 1 Chaos Ogryn per 10 Guardsmen — should show "/1"). Re-confirmed 2026-06-21 against `Chaos Space Marines ENG.ods`: Traitor Guard "For each 10 models you may select 1 Chaos Ogryn"; Accursed Cultists "Per 5 Accursed Cultist models you may set up 1 Torment". FIXED with a new generic `Model.ratio_per_n`/`ratio_of` field pair — the stepper\'s effective max is now min(static max, floor(modelSizes[ratio_of] / ratio_per_n)) in both UnitCard.tsx render blocks (the min>0 stepper and the min=0 "Add-on" stepper), set to ratio_per_n:10/ratio_of:"Traitor Guardsman" on Chaos Ogryn and ratio_per_n:5/ratio_of:"Accursed Cultist" on Torment. A matching validator (defense in depth) catches a count that exceeds the ratio some other way, e.g. reducing the primary squad after the secondary count was already set, or a pasted army JSON.',
